text: Constance Moore (January 18, 1920 or 1921 âˆ’ September 16, 2005) was an American actress. She was best known for wartime musicals, including Atlantic City (1944), Show Business (also 1944) and Buck Rogers (1939). In the latter, she played Wilma Deering. Moore was born in Sioux City, Iowa. She was later raised in various places. She died in Los Angeles, California after a long illness and of heart failure. Many sources say Moore was born in 1920.
